FBIS3-31055 "dreeu031_b_94004" FBIS-EEU-94-031 Document Type:Daily Report 15 Feb 1994 BULGARIA Berov Explains Removal of Cabinet Secretary AU1002181494 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network in Bulgarian 1700 GMT 10 Feb 94 AU1002181494 Sofia Khorizont Radio Network Language: Bulgarian Article Type:BFN [Text] Prime Minister Lyuben Berov today stated his view that the reports in certain newspapers to the effect that Stoyan Denchev had active contacts with private business circles correspond to the truth, adding that this is incompatible with Denchev's position as chief secretary of the Council of Ministers. Denchev has reportedly been offered a diplomatic post in London or Helsinki, but apparently no official decision on the affair has yet been adopted.
